1) There should be an option to upload an image not pick image from gallery  of the phone in the Confirm Pickup section.

2.

There should be an API integration or validation method to ensure that only valid addresses are accepted on the website.

3.

The website should not get stuck on the Delivery Login or Admin Login pages.

When the delivery user or admin logs out, they should be redirected to the user page.

However, if they are already logged in, they should not be redirected to the user page.

They should be redirected to the user page only when they are not logged in.

4.

Cookies should be integrated into the website to maintain user sessions.

After refreshing the website, users should not be asked to log in again.

The login page should appear only if the session keys/cookies are deleted or expired.

5.

The Confirm Delivery button should be linked to the live location of the delivery agent.

The delivery should not be marked as confirmed immediately just by clicking the button.

The delivery agent must first upload an image as proof of delivery.

After the image is uploaded, the system should verify in real time whether the delivery agent has actually reached the correct delivery location.

This is necessary because fake delivery confirmations can happen, which can negatively affect the user experience.